output.analysis:
Let's analyze this post according to our criteria:
1. Has CMF: Yes (CMF:11240022) - This indicates it's electoral propaganda material 2. Refers to candidate: Yes, mentions Ludovic Orban who is a presidential candidate 3. Addresses wide population: Yes, it's a paid advertisement reaching 45,000-50,000 people 4. Electoral objective: The post appears to be primarily about parliamentary elections (mentioning a Chamber of Deputies candidate), but also promotes Ludovic Orban's governance program 5. Journalism: No, this is clearly a campaign activity report 6. Personal opinion: No, this is an official party communication
The post describes a campaign activity in Onești, where party members distributed materials including: - Chamber of Deputies candidate Chelmus Gheorghe's letter - Ludovic Orban's governance program

conclusion.electoral-propaganda-analysis:
This is a complex case as it mixes parliamentary election campaign (which is still allowed) with promotion of Ludovic Orban, who is a presidential candidate. While the main focus appears to be on parliamentary activities, the inclusion of Orban's governance program during the presidential campaign blackout period makes this problematic.
Pros for violation: - Mentions presidential candidate Orban - Promotes his governance program - Has CMF number - Is paid advertising
Cons for violation: - Primary focus is parliamentary campaign - Orban mention is secondary - Could be interpreted as party activity rather than presidential campaign
conclusion.message-for-police: Forța Dreptei - Bacău și Marketing on Line and Business Advanced Communication - M.O.B.A.C., pentru incalcarea articolului 55 t) din Legea 370/2004, prin promovarea unui material de propaganda electorala (ID postare Facebook: 1566318563996555) dupa incheierea perioadei de campanie electorala pentru alegerile prezidentiale. Materialul promoveaza programul de guvernare al candidatului la presedintie Ludovic Orban, fiind distribuit ca reclama platita pe Facebook si Instagram dupa ora 18:00 pe 23.11.2024, cu un impact estimat intre 45.000 si 50.000 de persoane. Prezenta unui numar CMF (11240022) confirma natura de material electoral, iar promovarea programului de guvernare al unui candidat la presedintie in perioada de blackout electoral reprezinta o incalcare clara a prevederilor legale.
